fields.name: Elon Musk
fields.description: Elon Musk is a business magnate and investor. He is the founder, CEO, and chief engineer of SpaceX; angel investor, CEO, and product architect of Tesla, Inc.; owner and CEO of Twitter, Inc.; founder of The Boring Company; co-founder of Neuralink and OpenAI; and president of the Musk Foundation.

fields.name: Mark Zuckerberg
fields.description: Mark Zuckerberg is an American computer programmer and internet entrepreneur. He is the co-founder and CEO of Facebook, one of the most popular social networking websites in the world. Zuckerberg is also the co-founder of the Chan Zuckerberg Initiative, a philanthropic organization that focuses on education, health care, and scientific research.

fields.name: Larry Page
fields.description: Larry Page is the co-founder of Google and Alphabet Inc. He is a computer scientist and engineer who is known for his work on the PageRank algorithm, which is used to rank websites in Google's search engine. Page is also known for his vision for the future of technology, and he has been a vocal advocate for artificial intelligence and self-driving cars.

fields.name: Richard Branson
fields.description: Richard Branson is a British business magnate, investor, author, and philanthropist. He is the founder of the Virgin Group, a multinational conglomerate that owns over 400 companies in various industries, including transportation, telecommunications, media, and tourism. Branson is also the founder of Virgin Galactic, a space tourism company.

fields.name: Steve Jobs
fields.description: Steve Jobs was the co-founder, chairman, and chief executive officer of Apple Inc. He was a charismatic and visionary leader who helped to revolutionize the personal computer, music, and mobile phone industries. Jobs was born in San Francisco, California, in 1955. He was adopted by Paul and Clara Jobs, who raised him in Mountain View, California. Jobs dropped out of Reed College after one semester, but he continued to study calligraphy and Eastern philosophy.

fields.name: Larry Ellison
fields.description: Larry Ellison is an American business magnate, investor, and philanthropist. He is the co-founder, executive chairman, chief technology officer (CTO), and former chief executive officer (CEO) of Oracle Corporation. As of February 2023, he was listed by Bloomberg Billionaires Index as the sixth-wealthiest person in the world, with an estimated fortune of $102.6 billion. Ellison is also known for his 98% ownership stake in Lanai, the sixth-largest island in the Hawaiian Archipelago.

fields.name: Steve Ballmer
fields.description: Steve Ballmer is an American business executive who served as the CEO of Microsoft from 2000 to 2014. He is currently the owner of the Los Angeles Clippers of the National Basketball Association (NBA). Ballmer was born in Detroit, Michigan, and attended Harvard University, where he graduated with a degree in economics. After graduating from Harvard, Ballmer worked as a product manager at Procter & Gamble. He then joined Microsoft in 1980, where he held various positions, including executive vice president of sales and support, and president of the Windows division. In 2000, Ballmer was named CEO of Microsoft, succeeding Bill Gates. As CEO, Ballmer oversaw the company's growth into a diversified technology company, and he also led the company's acquisition of several major companies, including Skype and LinkedIn. Ballmer stepped down as CEO of Microsoft in 2014, and he was succeeded by Satya Nadella.

fields.name: Mukesh Ambani
fields.description: Mukesh Dhirubhai Ambani is an Indian business tycoon who is the chairman and managing director of Reliance Industries Limited (RIL), one of the largest conglomerates in India. He is the richest person in India with a net worth of $88.8 billion as of March 2023.

fields.name: Oprah Winfrey
fields.description: Oprah Winfrey is an American talk show host, actress, producer, and philanthropist. She is best known for her talk show, The Oprah Winfrey Show, which was the highest-rated television program of its kind in history and was nationally syndicated from 1986 to 2011.

fields.name: Jack Dorsey
fields.description: Jack Dorsey is an American internet entrepreneur, philanthropist, and software engineer. He is the co-founder and former CEO of Twitter, Inc., as well as co-founder, principal executive officer and chairperson of Block, Inc., the developer of the Square financial services platform.

fields.name: Raymond Thomas Dalio
fields.description: Raymond Thomas Dalio (born August 8, 1949)[1] is an American billionaire investor and hedge fund manager, who has served as co-chief investment officer of the world's largest hedge fund, Bridgewater Associates, since 1985. He founded Bridgewater in 1975 in New York. A $5 million investment from the World Bank's retirement fund was made within five years.

fields.name: Jack Ma
fields.description: Jack Ma is a Chinese business magnate, investor, and philanthropist. He is the co-founder and former executive chairman of Alibaba Group, a multinational technology conglomerate. As of March 2023, with a net worth of $33.3 billion, Ma is the fifth-wealthiest person in China (after Zhong Shanshan, Zhang Yiming, Ma Huateng, and Robin Zeng), as well as the 63rd wealthiest person in the world, ranked by Bloomberg Billionaires Index.

fields.name: Shiv Nadar
fields.description: Nadar was born in 1945 in a small village in Tamil Nadu, India. He studied engineering at the Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur, and then worked for a few years at the National Institute of Technology, Tiruchirappalli. In 1976, he founded HCL with five friends. The company started out as a manufacturer of calculators and microprocessors, but it later shifted its focus to software development.

fields.name: Adam D’Angelo
fields.description: Adam D'Angelo (born August 21, 1984) is an American internet entrepreneur. He is best known as the co-founder and CEO of Quora, based in Mountain View, California. He was the chief technology officer of Facebook, and also served as its vice president of engineering, until 2008.[1][2] In June 2009, he started Quora.[3] He invested $20 million of his own money into Quora as part of their Series B round of financing.[4] He is a member of the board of directors of OpenAI.

Ratan Tata is an Indian business tycoon who was the chairman of the Tata Group, one of the largest conglomerates in India, from 1991 to 2012. He is known for his business acumen, his commitment to social responsibility, and his philanthropy.

Tata was born in Bombay, India, in 1937. He studied architecture at Cornell University and then worked for the family business, Tata Sons. He rose through the ranks of the company, and in 1991, he was appointed chairman.

fields.name: Nithin Kamath
fields.description:
Nithin Kamath is the co-founder and CEO of Zerodha, an Indian discount stockbroker. He is one of the youngest self-made billionaires in India, with a net worth of $2.7 billion.

Kamath was born in Mangalore, Karnataka, India, in 1981. He studied engineering at the Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay, and then worked as a software engineer for a few years. In 2010, he founded Zerodha with his brother, Nikhil Kamath.

fields.name: Manish Sharma
fields.description:

Manish Sharma is the chief operating officer of Accenture, a global professional services company. He is responsible for leading the company's global business operations, executing its business strategy, protecting its people and infrastructure, and ensuring operational excellence. Sharma has over 25 years of experience in the IT industry, and he has held a variety of leadership positions at Accenture. He is a member of the company's Global Management Committee, and he is a frequent speaker at industry events.

fields.name: Parag Agrawal
fields.description: Parag Agrawal is an Indian-American software engineer and businessman. He was the CEO of Twitter, Inc. from November 2021 to October 2022. He was appointed CEO by Twitter co-founder Jack Dorsey, who stepped down from the role. Agrawal had previously served as CTO of Twitter since October 2017.

fields.name: Rangarajan Raghuram
fields.description: Mr. Rangarajan (Raghu) Raghuram is the Chief Executive Officer at Vmware Inc. He earned his M. Tech. Degree in Electrical Engineering from IIT Bombay in 1986 and his MBA from Wharton School of Business, University of Pennsylvania, in 1996.

fields.name: Arvind Krishna
fields.description: Arvind Krishna is an Indian-American business executive serving as the Chairman and CEO of IBM. He has been the CEO of IBM since April 2020 and took on the role of Chairman in January 2021

fields.name: Sundar Pichai
fields.description:
Sundar Pichai is an Indian-American business executive who is the chief executive officer of Alphabet Inc. and its subsidiary Google. He has been in this role since October 24, 2015, and is the first non-white CEO of a major U.S. technology company.

Pichai was born in Madurai, India, and studied engineering at the Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur and Stanford University. He then worked as a management consultant at McKinsey & Company before joining Google in 2004.

fields.name: Revathi Advaithi
fields.description:
Revathi Advaithi is an Indian-born American business executive. She is the CEO of Flex (formerly Flextronics) and is an advocate for women in STEM and in the workplace. Prior to joining Flex in 2019, Advaithi worked in various leadership positions at Eaton and Honeywell.

Advaithi was born in India in 1967 to A.N.N Swamy, a chemical engineer, and Visalam Swamy, a homemaker. Advaithi has four sisters. Her family lived in Bihar, Gujarat, and Assam before finally settling in Chennai, India. Advaithi met her husband Jeevan Mulgund in Hutchinson, KS and they married in 1998. Mulgund and Advaithi have since lived in England, Shanghai, Phoenix, AZ, and Pittsburgh, PA, and they are currently residing in the San Francisco Bay Area. They have two children. Advaithi is a passionate advocate for diversity and inclusion in the workforce, as well as STEM education for girls and computer science education.

fields.name: Leena Nair
fields.description:
Nair was born in Kolhapur, India, in 1969. She studied engineering at the Walchand College of Engineering in Sangli, India, and then earned an MBA from the Indian Institute of Management Ahmedabad.

Nair began her career at Unilever, where she held a variety of leadership positions in human resources and marketing. In 2016, she was appointed Unilever's Chief Human Resources Officer, becoming the first woman and first Asian to hold that position.

In 2021, Nair was appointed Global Chief Executive Officer of Chanel. She is the first woman of color to lead a major luxury fashion house.

Nair is a strong advocate for diversity and inclusion in the workplace. She is also a champion of women's empowerment. She is a role model for women and girls around the world.

fields.name: Satya Nadella
fields.description: Satya Narayana Nadella is an Indian-American business executive. He is the executive chairman and CEO of Microsoft, succeeding Steve Ballmer in 2014 as CEO and John W. Thompson in 2021 as chairman.

fields.name: Jayashree Ullal
fields.description:
Jayashree Ullal is a British-American billionaire businesswoman, president, and CEO of Arista Networks, a cloud networking company responsible for the deployment of 10/25/40/50/100 Gigabit Ethernet networking in the data center.

Ullal was born on March 27, 1961, in London into a Hindu family of Indian origin. She resided in New Delhi, India during her school years and eventually attended San Francisco State University, where she graduated with a B.S. in engineering (electrical). She went on to Santa Clara University where she received a master's degree in engineering management.

After graduating from Santa Clara, Ullal began her career at Sun Microsystems, where she held a variety of engineering and management positions. In 1998, she joined Cisco Systems, where she rose through the ranks to become the company's senior vice president of worldwide sales and marketing.

fields.name: Anjali Sud
fields.description:
Anjali Sud is the CEO of Vimeo, a video-sharing platform. She was appointed to the position in July 2017, after previously serving as General Manager and head of marketing.

Sud was born in Detroit, Michigan, in 1983. She attended Phillips Academy in Andover, Massachusetts, and then went on to earn a bachelor's degree in economics from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania and an MBA from Harvard Business School.

After graduating from Harvard, Sud worked as a management consultant at McKinsey & Company. She then joined Google, where she held a variety of marketing and product management roles. In 2014, she was appointed head of marketing for Vimeo.

As CEO of Vimeo, Sud has focused on expanding the company's reach and making it easier for users to create and share high-quality video content. She has also led the company's efforts to develop new products and services, such as Vimeo Create, a video editing app, and Vimeo OTT, a platform for streaming video to connected devices.

fields.name: Alex Hormozi
fields.description: Alex Hormozi is an entrepreneur and business coach known for his expertise in the fitness and gym industry. Hormozi gained popularity for his strategies and systems to help gym owners increase revenue and improve their business operations.

fields.name: Ankur Warikoo
fields.description: Ankur Warikoo is currently a serial entrepreneur, bestselling author, online educator, and content creator. He is also an active angel investor in 30+ companies and loves to spend time with first-time entrepreneurs mentoring them.

fields.name: Gerald Ford
fields.description: Gerald Rudolph Ford Jr. was the 38th president of the United States, serving from 1974 to 1977. He was the only president who was never elected to either the presidency or vice presidency, having been appointed vice president by Richard Nixon and then assuming the presidency upon Nixon's resignation.

fields.name: Jimmy Carter
fields.description: Jimmy Carter was the 39th president of the United States, serving from 1977 to 1981. He was a peanut farmer and engineer from Georgia who entered politics in the 1960s. He served as governor of Georgia from 1971 to 1975. Carter was elected president in 1976, defeating incumbent Gerald Ford.

fields.name: Ronald Reagan
fields.description:
Ronald Reagan was the 40th president of the United States, serving from 1981 to 1989. He was a conservative Republican who was known for his strong stance against communism and his belief in limited government.

Reagan was born in Tampico, Illinois, in 1911. He worked as an actor and a radio personality before entering politics. He served as governor of California from 1967 to 1975.

fields.name: George H. W. Bush
fields.description: George Herbert Walker Bush was an American politician, diplomat, and businessman who served as the 41st president of the United States from 1989 to 1993.

fields.name: Bill Clinton
fields.description:
Bill Clinton served as the 42nd president of the United States from 1993 to 2001. He was the first baby boomer president, and he is the husband of former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton.

Clinton was born William Jefferson Blythe III on August 19, 1946, in Hope, Arkansas. His father died in a car accident three months before he was born, and his mother remarried when he was four years old. Clinton took his stepfather's last name, Cassidy.

fields.name: George W. Bush
fields.description:
George W. Bush served as the 43rd president of the United States from 2001 to 2009. He is the eldest son of the 41st president, George H. W. Bush, and Barbara Bush.

Bush was born in New Haven, Connecticut, on July 6, 1946. He grew up in Texas and graduated from Yale University and Harvard Business School. After working in the oil industry, he entered politics in 1978, when he was elected to the U.S. House of Representatives. He served in the House for six years before being elected governor of Texas in 1994.

fields.name: Donald Trump
fields.description:
Donald Trump was the 45th president of the United States. He was born on June 14, 1946, in Queens, New York. He is a businessman and television personality.

Trump attended the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania with a bachelor's degree in economics. After graduating, Trump took over his family's real estate business, which he renamed The Trump Organization.

Trump built a successful business empire, but he also made many enemies along the way. He was accused of fraud, discrimination, and sexual assault. In 1990, he filed for bankruptcy six times.

fields.name: Joe Biden
fields.description:
Joe Biden is the 46th and current president of the United States. He was born on November 20, 1942, in Scranton, Pennsylvania. He is a member of the Democratic Party.

Biden graduated from the University of Delaware and Syracuse Law School. He served in the New Castle County Council from 1972 to 1973 and the United States Senate from 1973 to 2009. He was the 47th vice president of the United States from 2009 to 2017 under President Barack Obama.

Biden was elected president in 2020, defeating incumbent president Donald Trump. He is the oldest and first Roman Catholic president of the United States.

fields.name: Abraham Lincoln
fields.description:
1
Abraham Lincoln was the 16th president of the United States. He led the nation through the American Civil War, its bloodiest war, and perhaps its greatest moral, political, and constitutional crisis. In doing so, he preserved the Union, abolished slavery, strengthened the federal government, modernized the U.S. economy, and modernized U.S. society.

fields.name: Xi Jinping
fields.description: Xi Jinping is a Chinese politician who has served as the general secretary of the Chinese Communist Party and chairman of the Central Military Commission, and thus as the paramount leader of China, since 2012. Xi has also served as the president of the People's Republic of China since 2013.

fields.name: Vladimir Putin
fields.description:
Vladimir Putin has been in power in Russia for a total of 16 years, including a year-long acting term, two four-year terms, and two six-year terms. He was first elected as president in 2000 and was re-elected in 2004, 2012, and again in 2018. He is currently eligible for re-election in 2024.

Putin's time in power has been marked by both controversy and stability. He has been praised for his economic reforms, which have helped to raise living standards in Russia. However, he has also been criticized for his authoritarian rule, his human rights record, and his involvement in the Syrian civil war.

fields.name: Angela Merkel
fields.description: Angela Merkel was the Chancellor of Germany from 2005 to 2021. She was the first female chancellor of Germany and the longest-serving chancellor in German history. Merkel was a member of the Christian Democratic Union (CDU) and is considered to be a centrist politician.

fields.name: Will Smith
fields.description: Will Smith is an American actor, rapper, and producer. He has won four Grammy Awards, an Academy Award, and a BAFTA Award. As of 2023, his films have grossed over $9.3 billion globally, making him one of Hollywood's most bankable stars.

fields.name: Meryl Streep
fields.description:
Meryl Streep is an American actress who has won three Academy Awards, eight Golden Globe Awards, and 21 Screen Actors Guild Awards, more than any other actor or actress. She has been nominated for a record 21 Academy Awards, winning three for Kramer vs. Kramer (1979), Sophie's Choice (1982), and The Iron Lady (2011).

Streep was born in Summit, New Jersey, in 1949. She began her acting career in the early 1970s and has appeared in over 100 films. She is known for her versatility and her ability to portray a wide range of characters.

Some of Streep's most notable films include Kramer vs. Kramer, Sophie's Choice, The Deer Hunter, Out of Africa, Silkwood, The French Lieutenant's Woman, The Bridges of Madison County, The Devil Wears Prada, Doubt, Mamma Mia!, and Florence Foster Jenkins.

Streep is also a respected stage actress. She has won two Tony Awards for her work in the musicals A Chorus Line and The Seagull.

fields.name: George Clooney
fields.description:
George Timothy Clooney is an American actor, director, producer, and screenwriter. He is known for his work in films such as Ocean's Eleven, Up in the Air, and The Descendants. He has won two Academy Awards, one for Best Supporting Actor for his role in Syriana and one for Best Picture as one of the producers for Argo.

Clooney was born in Lexington, Kentucky, and raised in Augusta, Ohio. He studied acting at the University of Cincinnati College-Conservatory of Music. After graduating, he moved to Los Angeles to pursue a career in acting.

Clooney's first major role was in the television series ER, for which he won two Golden Globe Awards. He has since starred in a number of successful films, including Ocean's Eleven, Up in the Air, and The Descendants. He has also directed and produced several films, including Good Night and Good Luck, Michael Clayton, and The Descendants.

fields.name: Johnny Depp
fields.description: Johnny Depp is an American actor, producer, and musician. He has won the Golden Globe Award for Best Actor – Motion Picture Musical or Comedy twice, for Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street (2008) and Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End (2011), and has been nominated for three Academy Awards.

Kishore Biyani is an Indian billionaire businessman who is the founder and former CEO of Future Group, one of India's largest retail conglomerates. He is known for pioneering the concept of modern retail in India with his Big Bazaar chain of hypermarkets.

fields.name: Shah Rukh Khan
fields.description: Shah Rukh Khan is an Indian actor and film producer who works in Hindi films. He is one of the most popular and successful actors in the world. He has appeared in over 100 films and has won numerous awards, including 14 Filmfare Awards.

fields.name: Emma Watson
fields.description: Emma Watson is an English actress and model. She is best known for her role as Hermione Granger in the Harry Potter film series. She has also starred in films such as Beauty and the Beast, Little Women, and The Perks of Being a Wallflower.

fields.name: Paul Graham
fields.description:
Paul Graham is an American computer programmer, entrepreneur, and essayist. He is best known as one of the co-founders of the Y Combinator startup accelerator and for his essays on technology, entrepreneurship, and culture.

Graham was born in 1964 in England. He studied computer science at Harvard University and then worked as a software engineer at Apple Computer and Viaweb. In 1995, he co-founded Y Combinator with Jessica Livingston and Robert Tappan Morris.

fields.name: Ev William
fields.description: Ev Williams is an American technology entrepreneur and investor. He is the co-founder of several successful companies, including Blogger, Twitter, and Medium. He is also the founder of Obvious Ventures, a venture capital firm that invests in early-stage technology companies.

fields.name: Patrick Collison
fields.description: Patrick Collison is an Irish billionaire entrepreneur and the co-founder and CEO of Stripe, a financial technology company that provides payment processing software and APIs for online businesses. He was born in Dromineer, County Tipperary, Ireland, on September 9, 1988. He attended Castletroy College in Limerick, Ireland, and then the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), where he graduated with a degree in computer science in 2010.

fields.name: Tim O’Reilly
fields.description: Timothy O'Reilly is an Irish-American author and publisher, who is the founder of O'Reilly Media. He popularised the terms open source and Web 2.0.

fields.name: Taylor Swift
fields.description: Taylor Alison Swift is an American singer-songwriter. She is known for her narrative songwriting, which often centers around themes of love, heartbreak, and revenge. Swift has released nine studio albums, all of which have been commercially successful.

fields.name: Fareed Zakaria
fields.description: Fareed Zakaria is an Indian-American journalist, political commentator, and author. He is the host of CNN's Fareed Zakaria GPS and writes a weekly paid column for The Washington Post. He has been a columnist for Newsweek, editor of Newsweek International, and an editor at large of Time.

fields.name: leila hormozi
fields.description: Leila Hormozi is a first-generation Iranian-American entrepreneur, investor, and philanthropist. In 2015, Leila moved to Orange County, California to start a career in fitness. Within a year of moving, she was the top-selling personal trainer within the region and kept that status for the remainder of her tenure. fields.description: Allahbadia started his YouTube channel in 2014 with the goal of helping people live healthier and more fulfilling life. His channel has since grown to over 7 million subscribers, and he has become one of the most popular fitness and lifestyle YouTubers in India.

Ishant Sharma is an Indian cricketer who plays for Delhi and the Indian national team. He is a right-arm fast bowler who is known for his ability to generate pace and bounce. Sharma made his Test debut for India in 2007 and has since played over 100 Tests, taking over 300 wickets. He has also played over 100 ODIs and T20Is.

fields.name: Hillary Clinton
fields.description: Hillary Clinton is an American politician who served as the 67th United States Secretary of State from 2009 to 2013, as a United States Senator from New York from 2001 to 2009, and as the first lady of the United States as the wife of President Bill Clinton from 1993 to 2001.

fields.name: Michelle Obama
fields.description:
Michelle Obama is the 44th First Lady of the United States. She is the wife of President Barack Obama and the mother of two daughters, Malia and Sasha.

Michelle Obama was born in Chicago, Illinois, in 1964. She graduated from Princeton University and Harvard Law School. After law school, she worked as a lawyer and a community organizer.

fields.name: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez
fields.description:
Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez is an American politician who has served as the U.S. Representative for New York's 14th congressional district since 2019. A member of the Democratic Party, she is the youngest woman ever elected to Congress.

Ocasio-Cortez was born in the Bronx, New York City, and raised in Yorktown Heights, New York. She graduated from Boston University with a degree in economics and international relations. After college, she worked as a bartender and waitress while working on her political campaigns.

fields.name: David Deutsch
fields.description:
David Deutsch is a British physicist who is known for his work in quantum computation and quantum theory. He is a visiting professor at the University of Oxford and a fellow of Wolfson College, Oxford.

Deutsch was born in Haifa, Israel, in 1953. He studied physics at the University of Cambridge and received his PhD in 1980. After completing his Ph.D., he worked as a research fellow at the University of Oxford.

fields.name: Donald Knuth
fields.description:
Donald Knuth is an American computer scientist and mathematician. He is known for his work on algorithms, typesetting, and programming languages. He is the author of the seminal work The Art of Computer Programming, which is considered to be one of the most important books in computer science.

Knuth was born in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, in 1938. He received his Ph.D. from the University of California, Berkeley, in 1963. He has been a professor at Stanford University since 1968.

fields.name: Neil deGrasse Tyson
fields.description: Neil deGrasse Tyson is an American astrophysicist, author, and science communicator. Tyson is the Frederick P. Rose Director of the Hayden Planetarium at the American Museum of Natural History in New York City. He is also the host of the television show Cosmos: A Spacetime Odyssey and the podcast StarTalk Radio.

fields.name: Lex Fridman
fields.description: Lex Fridman is a research scientist at MIT and the host of the popular Lex Fridman Podcast. He is a graduate of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) and holds a PhD in Robotics from the university. Fridman's research interests include artificial intelligence, machine learning, and computer vision. He has published over 20 papers in top academic conferences and journals.

fields.name: Lewis Cantley
fields.description: Lewis C. Cantley is an American cell biologist and biochemist who has made significant advances to the understanding of cancer metabolism. Among his most notable contributions are the discovery and study of the enzyme PI-3-kinase, now known to be important to understanding cancer and diabetes mellitus.

fields.name: Jonathan Eisen
fields.description: Jonathan Andrew Eisen is an American evolutionary biologist, currently working at the University of California, Davis. His academic research is in the fields of evolutionary biology, genomics, and microbiology and he is the academic editor-in-chief of the open-access journal PLOS Biology.

fields.name: A. P. J. Abdul Kalam
fields.description: Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam was an Indian aerospace scientist and statesman who served as the 11th president of India from 2002 to 2007. He was born and raised in Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu and studied physics and aerospace engineering. He spent the next four decades as a scientist and science administrator, mainly at the Defence Research and Development Organisation (DRDO) and Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) and was intimately involved in India's civilian space programme and military missile development efforts.

fields.name: Vikram Sarabhai
fields.description: Vikram Sarabhai was an Indian scientist and industrialist who is considered the father of the Indian space program. He was born in Ahmedabad, Gujarat, India, on August 12, 1919. He studied physics at the University of Cambridge and then returned to India to work in the textile industry. In 1947, he founded the Physical Research Laboratory in Ahmedabad, which became a leading research center in India.

fields.name: Homi J. Bhabha
fields.description: Homi Jehangir Bhabha (30 October 1909 – 24 January 1966) was an Indian nuclear physicist who is widely credited as the "father of the Indian nuclear programme". He was the founding director and professor of physics at the Tata Institute of Fundamental Research (TIFR), as well as the founding director of the Atomic Energy Establishment, Trombay (AEET) which was renamed the Bhabha Atomic Research Centre in his honour. TIFR and AEET served as the cornerstone of the Indian nuclear energy and weapons programme. He was the first chairman of the Indian Atomic Energy Commission and secretary of the Department of Atomic Energy.

fields.name: C. V. Raman
fields.description: Sir Chandrasekhara Venkata Raman FRS was an Indian physicist known for his work in the field of light scattering. Using a spectrograph that he developed, he and his student K. S. Krishnan discovered that when light traverses a transparent material, the deflected light changes its wavelength and frequency.
